---
// The problem: "long-running AI work hits two walls" (from the README).
// Parallax lives on decorative blobs; content reveals on scroll.
---

<section class="section problem" id="why">
  <div class="backdrop" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="blob blob-a parallax parallax-slow"></div>
    <div class="blob blob-b parallax parallax-mid"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <p class="kicker reveal reveal-sm">The failure mode</p>
    <h2 class="reveal">Long-running AI work hits two walls.</h2>

    <div class="cards">
      <article class="card reveal">
        <span class="num">01</span>
        <h3>A fresh session starts blank.</h3>
        <p>
          Every "where were we?" is re-derived from scratch, or re-explained by you, for the tenth
          time.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card reveal">
        <span class="num">02</span>
        <h3>A long session fills its context.</h3>
        <p>
          Mid-task the window overflows and the agent forgets its own earlier decisions, then
          confidently contradicts them an hour later.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="closer reveal">
      The usual answer is <em>conventions</em>: "keep a decisions log," "write a handoff." But
      conventions rot, because nothing executes them. Clauderizer keeps the proven model and makes
      it a <strong>system</strong>, not a hope.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--ink-900), var(--ink-800));
  }
  .backdrop {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .blob {
    position: absolute;
    border-radius: 50%;
    filter: blur(64px);
  }
  .blob-a {
    width: 42rem;
    height: 42rem;
    left: -12rem;
    top: -10rem;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(139, 145, 161, 0.16), transparent 65%);
  }
  .blob-b {
    width: 40rem;
    height: 40rem;
    right: -14rem;
    bottom: -12rem;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, var(--amber-glow), transparent 62%);
  }
  .container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 22rem), 1fr));
    gap: 1.2rem;
    margin-top: 2.6rem;
  }
  .card {
    background: rgba(18, 21, 29, 0.66);
    border: 1px solid var(--edge);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.7rem;
    backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
  }
  .card .num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--amber-400);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .card h3 {
    margin: 0.6rem 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
  }
  .card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--cream-200);
  }
  .closer {
    margin-top: 2.6rem;
    max-width: 48rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.8vw, 1.2rem);
    color: var(--cream-200);
  }
  .closer strong {
    color: var(--amber-400);
  }
</style>
